  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 15 airports right now. Engine anti-ice operations are flagged at Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO). Across base airports: 3 critical, 7 high, 11 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Iaşi (IAS/LRIA) and Craiova (CRA/LRCV); plus 7 other bases. 11 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV) and Václav Havel Airport Prague (PRG/LKPR). Network hotspots: Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Marche (AOI/LIPY) and 10 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, RVR limitations and very low visibility. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Göteborg Landvetter (GOT/ESGG), Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ) and 9 others.",
